---
name: FixStubbornBugsFastByParallelizing
description: Fix stubborn configuration and integration bugs fast by testing 8-10 different solution approaches in parallel. Build minimal test harness, systematically evaluate all approaches simultaneously, identify what works and why. Best for framework/library bugs with unclear root cause where serial debugging would take hours. Includes concrete examples, gotchas, checklists, and anti-patterns.
---

# Debugging Methodology: Parallel Solution Testing

**When a complex bug has an unclear root cause, systematically testing 8-10 different solution approaches in parallel is often faster and more thorough than serial trial-and-error.**

---

## Summary

**Parallel solution testing is a systematic methodology for complex bugs:**

1. **Identify** 8-10 orthogonally different approaches
2. **Build** minimal test harness showing all approaches simultaneously
3. **Test** all approaches in one run
4. **Analyze** why winner works and losers fail
5. **Apply** fix to production with deep understanding
6. **Debug** any context differences between test and production

**Best for:** Configuration/integration bugs in complex subsystems where root cause is ambiguous.

**Time investment:** 1-2 hours to build test harness, but saves hours/days of serial trial-and-error.

**Key success factors:** Platform compatibility, realistic test data, comprehensive logging, matching production context.

**Related methodologies:** Binary Search Debugging (bisecting commits), Fuzzing (input space exploration), Property-Based Testing (behavior space), A/B Testing (production comparison), Ablation Testing (component removal). This methodology is specifically optimized for **configuration/integration debugging**.

